COVID Wastewater Surveillance for Western Massachusetts

Regional, County, and Sewer Level COVID Wastewater Concentration

Regional Concentration and Wastewater Viral Activity Levels

From 2024-02-12 to 2025-02-10
Current WVA level: low
Current WVA score: 2.4

The above figure shows the regional wastewater COVID concentration for 10 sewer systems in Berkshire, Hampden, Hampshire, and Franklin counties. The trend line is a smoothed conditional mean. Each point is an individual system report. Both are weighted by population and reporting interval. WVA levels were calculated using the CDC methodology, except the (1 year) baseline is updated each time the WVA is calculated.

County-level Concentration

The above figure shows the county-level wastewater COVID concentration for 10 sewer systems in Berkshire, Hampden, Hampshire, and Franklin counties. The trend line is a smoothed conditional mean, weighted by population and reporting interval. Each point is an individual system report.

Concentration for Individual Sewer Systems 

The above figure shows reported concentration data from individual systems, with linear interpolation between reports of varying frequency. Gaps of longer than one week are not interpolated. Blue annotations indicate date of last data reported.

Data Sources
• CDC methodology: [https://www.cdc.gov/nwss/about-data.html#data-method]
• Wastewater data access: [https://www.mass.gov/info-details/wastewater-surveillance-reporting]
• Population weights are from various sources (EPA estimates whenever available).
